<div class="content" name="DOMAIN_SERVER_ENABLE_STATE" uuid="5b1a45c9-937e-4129-bec4-593f64c56d48"><p>The DOMAIN_SERVER_ENABLE_STATE enumeration describes the
enabled or disabled state of a server.</p><dl>
<dd>
<div><pre> typedef  enum _DOMAIN_SERVER_ENABLE_STATE
 {
   DomainServerEnabled = 1,
   DomainServerDisabled
 } DOMAIN_SERVER_ENABLE_STATE,
  *PDOMAIN_SERVER_ENABLE_STATE;
</pre></div>
</dd></dl><p><b>DomainServerEnabled:  </b>The server is considered
&#34;enabled&#34; to the client.</p><p><b>DomainServerDisabled:  </b>This field is not used.</p></div>